    "Reason : 1 - The London Borough of Hounslow as the Local Planning Authority hereby certify that on 05/11/2024, the proposal as shown on the drawing(s) submitted on 05/11/2024 and numbered AA-80167 / E01, AA-80167 / E02, AA-80167 / P01, AA-80167 / P02 was not lawful within the meanings of Section 191 and 192 of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990. \r\nThe development fails to comply with the terms of Class B, Paragraph B1, Clause (d) (ii) of Part 1 of Schedule 2 of the Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development) (England) Order 2015 (as amended) because the resulting roof space of the proposed extension would increase the cubic content of the original roof space by more than 50 cubic metres.\r\n"
